trans-unit.source: Defines an identifier for application domains that a cache implementation can use to interact with a host environment.
trans-unit.target: Definerer en ID for programdomener en hurtigbuffer implementering kan bruke til å kommunisere med en vertsmiljøet.

trans-unit.source: A [!INCLUDE[dnprdnshort](~/add/includes/dnprdnshort-md.md)] host environment such as ASP.NET can use the IApplicationIdentifier interface to define strings that identify individual application domains.
trans-unit.target: En [!INCLUDE[dnprdnshort](~/add/includes/dnprdnshort-md.md)] vertsmiljøet som ASP.NET kan bruke grensesnittet IApplicationIdentifier til å definere strenger som identifiserer individuelle programdomener.

trans-unit.source: The host environment implements the IApplicationIdentifier interface.
This interface is then available to <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ObjectCache> implementations through the <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ObjectCache.Host%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Dette grensesnittet deretter er tilgjengelig for <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ObjectCache>implementeringer via den <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ObjectCache.Host%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ObjectCache.Host%2A> </xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ObjectCache>

trans-unit.source: A cache implementation uses this reference to obtain an identifier for the application domain.
trans-unit.target: En hurtigbuffer implementering bruker denne referansen til å hente en identifikator for programdomenet.

trans-unit.source: In ASP.NET, cache implementations use the application identifier to construct identifiers for cache performance counters.
trans-unit.target: I ASP.NET Bruk hurtigbufferen implementeringer programidentifikatoren ikke konstruere identifikatorer for hurtigbufferen ytelsestellere.

trans-unit.source: This provides names for performance counter instances that can be distinguished between application domains when multiple application domains are running.
trans-unit.target: Dette gir navn for ytelse tellerforekomster som kan skilles mellom programdomener når flere programdomener kjører.

trans-unit.source: Gets an identifier for an application domain.
trans-unit.target: Henter en identifikator for et programdomene.

trans-unit.source: The GetApplicationId method is typically implemented by a [!INCLUDE[dnprdnshort](~/add/includes/dnprdnshort-md.md)] host environment in order to construct an application identifier for an <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ObjectCache> implementation.
trans-unit.target: Metoden GetApplicationId implementeres vanligvis av en [!INCLUDE[dnprdnshort](~/add/includes/dnprdnshort-md.md)] vertsmiljøet for å lage et program-ID for en <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ObjectCache>implementering.</xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ObjectCache>

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ObjectCache> implementation uses this information to identify the application domain that is currently running.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ObjectCache>implementering bruker denne informasjonen til å identifisere programdomenet som kjører.</xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ObjectCache>

trans-unit.source: For example, in ASP.NET, the cache uses an application identifier to construct identifiers for cache performance counters.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel i ASP.NET bruker hurtigbufferen en program-ID ikke konstruere identifikatorer for hurtigbufferen ytelsestellere.

trans-unit.source: The cache calls the GetApplicationId method that is implemented by the host environment and the host returns the identifier.
trans-unit.target: Hurtigbufferen kaller metoden GetApplicationId som implementeres av vertsmiljøet og verten returnerer IDen.

trans-unit.source: This provides names for performance counter instances that can be distinguished between application domains when multiple application domains are running.
trans-unit.target: Dette gir navn for ytelse tellerforekomster som kan skilles mellom programdomener når flere programdomener kjører.

trans-unit.source: A unique identifier for the current application domain.
trans-unit.target: En unik ID for gjeldende programdomenet.
